HEADWORD: Rattan
<hw>Rat*tan"</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧t*t⟦acr⟧n")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Malay
<ets>r⟦omac⟧tan</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>ratan</asp>.]</altsp> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of the long
slender flexible stems of several species of palms of the genus
<gen>Calamus</gen>, mostly East Indian, though some are African and
Australian. They are exceedingly tough, and are used for walking sticks,
wickerwork, chairs and seats of chairs, cords and cordage, and many
other purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

